player.seasonOutlook: The Buccaneers selected Darden in the fourth round of April's draft. The North Texas product is tiny (5-foot-9, 174 pounds) but super athletic, fast and quick with good tackle-breaking ability. He aligned in the slot 87% of the time at North Texas. Granted, it was light competition in the Conference USA, but Darden really exploded in 2020, with a massive 38% target share (second in this class) and 4.4 YPRR (fourth) to go along with a 74-1,190-19 receiving line. Darden's lack of size and strength may limit his production in downfield and contested situations, but he has the athleticism to be an NFL playmaker as a slot WR and punt returner. Darden won't see the field much in 2021 with Mike Evans, Chris Godwin, Antonio Brown and perhaps Scotty Miller and Tyler Johnson above him on the depth chart.
